 RESPONSIBILITIES            Work with key business stakeholders to develop business solutions based on data driven insights      Lead projects that combine diverse customer data sets to identify At FNBO, our employees are the heart of our story—and we’re committed to their success! Please see below the details of this career opportunity and how it fits into our organization’s success. The New Stockyard Group (NSG) is building a platform and ecosystem that levels the playing field across the beef supply chain—through leveraging cutting edge AI and blockchain technology, cattle can be digitally identified and tracked through all avenues of the chain. We are looking for an experienced full stack engineer who can build and own parts of the tech pipeline that will increase Ag producers’ access to future markets. You will spearhead prototyping, execution, and maintenance of critical company services while having a voice in the direction of the company. Reports directly to the Director of the NSG and works closely with the technical and product development teams to create experiences that provide lasting impacts to the beef supply chain. Key roles and responsibilities: Develop a strong understanding of our core product, the problem it’s solving and our customer base. Lead the development, deployment and maintenance of the Cattle ID application. Collaborate frequently with product management, developers, and the leadership team to create solutions that solve real world problems. Establish and maintain technology standards. Evaluate new tools and techniques that support the growth of the company. Stay up to date with new trends and technologies across cloud computing, mobile development, machine learning and security. Assist in hiring and training for new software engineers. Skills and Technologies Required: Ability to thrive and glide between a diverse set of projects in a fast-paced environment Excited about the prospect of tackling and deploying seemingly-impossible problems Passionate about providing equitable data access Experience with Flask, Express or similar web framework (API design is a plus) Experience with React and/or React Native (Expo Managed+Bare workflow is a plus) Strong communicator Cloud platform experience (preferably AWS) is a plus Bonus for familiarity with machine learning and/or blockchain Benefits: Flat organization structure Unlimited PTO and flexible scheduling Employer sponsored health care and 401k matching Connect as a team at our Downtown Omaha, NE HQ. This position provides a flexible remote work environment with in person collaboration opportunities. What is the NSG? The NSG is a consortium of Ag, financial, technology, and strategic partners working together to increase Ag producers’ access to future Ag markets. At FNBO, the NSG is building products that leverage AI and blockchain technology to solve real-world problems, ensuring agriculture producers maintain continued access to traditional markets while evolving to create new market opportunities. What is Cattle ID? Cattle ID is a blockchain-based system that identifies individual animals using facial-recognition technology and tracks their movement through the supply chain. It is currently deployed as a cross-platform React-native application. Ask us about getting an invite! Equity, Diversity, & Inclusion: FNBO is committed to belonging, inclusion, diversity and equity. We are committed to intentionally and proactively creating pathways to success for historically underrepresented populations. To accomplish this, we foster a culture of belonging and inclusion so that every employee is valued, and has opportunity and the ability to make an impact. FNBO strives to reflect the diversity of the communities we serve in the makeup of our workforce. See the full  FNBO Equity, Diversity, & Inclusion Statement  here All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or disability status.

Summary:     CSG’s Enterprise Public Cloud Practice is looking for a Data Scientist to join our Cloud FinOps Team. In this role you will use various data sets to find opportunities for cost, product, and process optimization. This role involves creating and using models to test the effectiveness of different courses of action. You will need to be passionate about using data to drive business outcomes. Join us as we continue the transformational work of building out CSG’s Cloud Practice.        Your primary responsibility will be using a variety of data mining/data analysis methods, using a variety of data tools, building, and implementing models, using/creating algorithms, and creating/running simulations. The outcomes of your work will inform the Cloud Financial Analysts and technical teams on spend efficiencies and optimization. The outcomes of your work will assist in building CSG’s future.        What you will be doing:         You will be working with the FinOps team, technical teams, and stakeholders throughout the business to solve cloud costing efficiencies with data informed decisions.      You will mine and analyze data from company databases, AWS/Azure datasets to drive optimization and improvement.      You will assess the effectiveness and accuracy of new data sources and data gathering techniques.      You will develop custom data models and algorithms to apply to data sets.      You will develop company A/B testing framework and test model quality.      You will coordinate with different functional teams to implement models and monitor outcomes.      You will develop processes and tools to monitor and analyze model performance and data accuracy.      You will use your strong technical aptitude and the people on your team to help gather and interpret requirements, create models, and develop timelines, manage execution, and communicate progress.           Requirements:         Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or IT related field or equivalent work experience.      Experience with statistical computer languages (R, Python, SQL, etc.) to manipulate data and draw insights from large data sets.      Experience working with and creating data architectures      Experience with modern software development methodologies and techniques. Posting Details  Position Information Job Title   Research Associate   Department   School of Interdisciplinary Informatics   Essential Functions  The College of Information Science and Technology at the University of Nebraska at Omaha invites applications for a Postdoctoral Research Associate. We seek to fill the postdoc position in Information Technology for our funded research project focused on bridge infrastructure health. The Postdoctoral Research Associate position will be for a period of 1 year, with the possibility for 1 to 2 more years of funded research work. This is a full-time, benefits eligible position. As a Postdoctoral Research Associate you will conduct research for 40 hours/week and supervise PhD, MS and undergraduate students as needed.  About the Research Project:  Using rural Nebraska bridges as full-scale “testbeds” we are conducting research and development on relating to data collection at the edge using internet of things including sensors, UAVs and more; secure data processing and management from the edge to the cloud; simulations visualizations and analytics of data using Machine Learning; sociotechnical impacts (perceived fairness of AI systems); and decision support systems.   The University and the College of Information Science and Technology have a strong commitment to achieving diversity among faculty and staff. The University of Nebraska does not discriminate based on race, color, ethnicity, national origin, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, and/or political affiliation in its programs, activities, or employment.  UNO  is a  VEVRAA  Federal Contractor and an E-Verify employer.    Work Schedule   M-F, 8 am - 5 pm   Additional Duties  Why  UNO ? The University of Nebraska at Omaha is fueled by its historical ties to Omaha. As the first municipal university in Omaha, the early founders’ goal was to make higher education accessible and affordable for the city’s residents. In 1968, the campus joined the University of Nebraska system, and today has the unique role of serving as the state’s metropolitan campus. Accessibility remains a top priority in UNO’s mission and vision. Today, the campus is known for its student-centered environment, its community engagement, and its dedication to embracing students from all types of backgrounds. UNO’s ranking as the 2020 Best College for LGBTQ+ Students In Nebraska reflects a commitment to the Maverick values of access, inclusion and diversity that make UNO a welcoming campus community, evidenced by the numerous resources and support services offered by the university.  The campus has built strong partnerships with local business, education, government, arts, and civic organizations in the city. UNO’s commitment to community engagement has landed UNO on the President’s Higher Education Community Service Honor Roll for seven consecutive years—the highest federal recognition a school can receive for civic engagement.  This honor is but one of many points of pride for UNO. In 2019, it was ranked in the top ten public institutions in the nation for military friendliness by Military Times magazine for the fifth consecutive year. Nearly 90 percent of UNO’s 15,500 students are from Nebraska, and roughly 60 percent of recent alumni surveyed report graduating with no debt or less than $5,000 in debt. It is simply one of the most competitively priced institutions in the region. UNO, while large enough to provide students with global opportunities, thrives on its personal and close-knit campus culture, where students come first and partnerships with the community grow every day. For more information about how UNO embraces its mission, see Growing With and Within Our Thriving Community.   Required Qualifications  Applicants must hold a PhD degree or the equivalent in computer science, informatics, information systems, information technology, or a closely related field. Applicants must have a demonstrated background in one or more of the following areas: optimization, visualization, cybersecurity, AI/ML, Internet of Things, and Data Analytics/Science. Applicants must have a demonstrated interest in research and development in the areas mentioned earlier. Evidence of this must be in the form of publications and thesis work. Applicants must be able to work independently and demonstrate good collaboration skills.   Preferred Qualifications   Physical Demands  The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Why            UNO           ?                             The University of Nebraska at Omaha is fueled by its historical ties to Omaha. As the first municipal university in Omaha, the early founders’ goal was to make higher education accessible and affordable for the city’s residents. In 1968, the campus joined the University of Nebraska system, and today has the unique role of serving as the state’s metropolitan campus.                            Accessibility remains a top priority in UNO’s mission and vision. Today, the campus is known for its student-centered environment, its community engagement, and its dedication to embracing students from all types of backgrounds. UNO’s ranking as the 2020 Best College for LGBTQ+ Students In Nebraska reflects a commitment to the Maverick values of access, inclusion and diversity that make UNO a welcoming campus community, evidenced by the numerous resources and support services offered by the university.                              The campus has built strong partnerships with local business, education, government, arts, and civic organizations in the city. UNO’s commitment to community engagement has landed UNO on the President’s Higher Education Community Service Honor Roll for seven consecutive years—the highest federal recognition a school can receive for civic engagement.                              This honor is but one of many points of pride for UNO. In 2019, it was ranked in the top ten public institutions in the nation for military friendliness by Military Times magazine for the fifth consecutive year. Nearly 90 percent of UNO’s 15,500 students are from Nebraska, and roughly 60 percent of recent alumni surveyed report graduating with no debt or less than $5,000 in debt. It is simply one of the most competitively priced institutions in the region. UNO, while large enough to provide students with global opportunities, thrives on its personal and close-knit campus culture, where students come first and partnerships with the community grow every day. Job Description Summary: We are hiring for a Data Scientist - someone who will help us unlock the value of our data and create decision guidance for our leaders. This role will support many departments across the company as well as upper-level management.     Job Description:     Responsibilities:     Happy Returns is growing at a rapid pace and is building a new team of Data Scientists. Scientists will be expected to work alongside current engineers to ensure existing tables accommodate the future needs of the business. Via this data structure, the team will effectively share insights across many departments including Sales, Warehouse Operations, Automation and HR. Insights will span historical reporting, as well as, planning and forecasting into the future. Machine learning, automation, and predictive modeling will be key to providing both accurate and timely reporting. You will have a chance to observe the impact of your work firsthand. More importantly, many departments across the company will be able to observe your impact firsthand. So – if the idea of building something from the ground up, working independently on highly visible projects, and immediate impact appeals to you, we want to hear from you. job_title: Senior Consultant, Senior Paid Social Media Buyer
job_Description: Position Summary         In today's world, customers expect companies to know who they are and what they want. Customers want to have products, services, or experiences that best suit their needs delivered to them seamlessly across physical and digital channels. Customers are human first: driven by dynamic wants, needs, and desires. The ability for brands to make personal, meaningful connections on a human level has never been greater and the Experience Management team at Deloitte Digital delivers on those experiences in a way that allows companies to own the customer journey end-to-end.         We help companies connect key data sources to understand what matters most to people; connect to advanced technologies like AI and machine learning to sense and respond to those needs at scale; and connect their systems to unlock insights, create collaboration and drive acquisition, engagement, and loyalty. Most importantly, we empower companies to connect with customers in personal, meaningful ways that respect them as people, not just customers.        The Experience Management team at Deloitte Digital gives companies the ability to build and leverage the connections - between people, systems, data, and technologies - so they can deliver personalized, contextual experiences to customers at scale. We are seeking to transform the way brands interact with their customers and elevate the human experience. Do you have data in your DNA? Join our growing team in supporting our clients' ability to communicate the right message to the right customers at the right time.           The Work You'll do         We are seeking a strong candidate that is passionate about social paid media, teamwork, process improvement, and driving results for clients. Attention to detail, positive energy, and a willingness to learn should be engrained in your DNA. You have a knack for digging into data and problem-solving your way to ROAS positive campaigns.        The Senior Paid Social Media Buyer will work across Deloitte Digital Clients, report to the Head of Ad Performance, and work as part of our Paid Media team. This person will be responsible for building and optimizing Facebook, LinkedIn, Pinterest, TikTok, and other paid social campaigns with the goal of achieving, and in many cases, exceeding clients' objectives and KPIs. The ideal candidate has a strong paid social planning, buying, and analysis background with experience executing/buying on social platforms. Additionally, you are looking to help mentor and up-level members of your team.            Build, manage and optimize paid social media campaigns through a variety of social platforms, specifically Facebook Ads Manager, TikTok, and YouTube (Pinterest and LinkedIn are a plus)      Develop paid social strategy to meet and exceed client's KPIs.      Utilize reporting to measure, evaluate, and analyze paid social campaign performance to determine campaign success and provide recommendations and optimizations on an ongoing basis.      Actively test and analyze targeting, ad creative, landing pages, and placements to drive results      Manage and pace campaign budgets on a routine basis to ensure efficient delivery of advertising spend and to ensure clients are pacing towards campaign objectives and goals      Work cross-functionally to align campaign strategies and goals across the paid media team in an effort to create more collaboration and ensure a holistic paid media approach and strategy      Create and present quarterly business reviews & other client-facing presentations that outline performance, insights from testing, and key strategic opportunities      Measure impact and effectiveness of campaigns and share results and insights with the paid media director and client contact      Stay current on paid social industry trends and emerging platforms      Delegate work to a paid social analyst who will support you on the account            The team         Advertising, Marketing & Commerce         Our Advertising, Marketing & Commerce team focuses on delivering marketing and growth objectives aligned with our clients' brand values for measurable business growth. We do this by creating content, communications, and experiences that engage and inspire their customers to act. We implement and operate the technology platforms that enable personalized content, commerce, and marketing user-centric experiences. In doing so, we transform our clients' marketing and engagement operations into modern, data-driven, creatively focused organizations. Our team brings deep experience in creative and digital marketing capabilities, many from our Digital Studios.        We serve our clients through the following types of work:            Omnichannel customer engagement strategy, design, and development (web, mobile, social, physical)      eCommerce strategy, implementation, and operations      Marketing Content and digital asset management solutions      Marketing Technology and Advertising Technology solutions      Marketing analytics implementation and operations      Advertising campaign ideation, development, and execution      Acquisition and engagement campaign ideation, development, and execution      Agile based, design-thinking, user-centric, empirical projects that accelerate results            Required Qualifications             4+ years of experience in paid social media buying and analysis      Experience in Facebook Ads Manager      In-depth knowledge of social media content requirements, restrictions, and best practices by platform - includes buying, optimizing, and reporting practices      Able to review results and performance of paid media campaigns based on predetermined success indicators, determine the effectiveness and report back to clients      Must be organized and able to work under multiple deadlines      Ability to collaborate in a team environment with a demonstrated ability to assist where needed      Willingness to dive in and find answers to complex problems where solutions may not yet be documented      Strong interpersonal and communication skills      Strong analytical and problem-solving skills      Initiative, detail orientation, strong analytical and decision-making skills      Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications      Bachelor of Arts or Bachelor of Science degree      Travel up to 30% (while 30% of travel is a requirement of the role, due to COVID-19, non-essential travel has been suspended until further notice)      Must be legally authorized to work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship now or at any time in the future            Preferred Qualifications             Facebook Blueprint certifications in Media Planning, Buying, etc.      Experience in the women's retail industry      Advertising Agency experience        AMC2021        XMAMC2022

Data Scientist  Overview:  The community has a need for timely and accurate COVID-19 results and information to protect themselves and others during this pandemic. GS Labs is responding to this call-to-action. We are prepared to provide this testing in a professional, safe environment and need reliable and detail-oriented people willing to join our team. If you feel called to contribute to the community in a meaningful way while earning a good wage, this opportunity might be for you.   What are we looking for?  We are looking for a Data Scientist to analyze large amounts of raw information to find patterns that will help improve our company. We will rely on you to build data products to extract valuable business insights. In this role, you should be highly analytical with a knack for analysis, math and statistics. Critical thinking and problem-solving skills are essential for interpreting data. We also want to see a passion for machine-learning and research. Your goal will be to help our company analyze trends to make better decisions.  Responsibilities  Identify valuable data sources and automate collection processes.  Undertake preprocessing of structured and unstructured data.  Analyze large amounts of information to discover trends and patterns.  Build predictive models and machine-learning algorithms.  Combine models through ensemble modeling.  Present information using data visualization techniques.  Propose solutions and strategies to business challenges.  Collaborate with engineering and product development teams.  Requirements  Proven experience as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst.  Experience in data mining.  Understanding of machine-learning and operations research.  Knowledge of R, SQL and Python; familiarity with Scala, Java or C++ is an asset.  Experience using business intelligence tools (e.g. Tableau) and data frameworks (e.g. Hadoop).  Analytical mind and business acumen.  Strong math skills (e.g. statistics, algebra).  Problem-solving aptitude.  Excellent communication and presentation skills.  BSc/BA in Computer Science, Engineering or relevant field; graduate degree in Data Science or other quantitative field is preferred.   What we offer:  Competitive pay and benefits program in a collaborative and fast paced work environment. Summary     The Business Intelligence Engineer utilizes industry standard data tools and methods for extracting, transforming, and loading data into a central data warehouse. This role provides expertise in data stewardship within the central data warehouse, across enterprise systems, and data pipelines. This position can be successfully preformed onsite or remote.     Essential Duties and Responsibilities    This description intends to describe the general nature and level of work performed by Teammates assigned to this job. It is not intended to include all duties, responsibilities, and qualifications. To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.         Create, automate, and manage integrations with existing company and vendor data systems.      Create and document data for reporting and analytical use cases.      Collaborate with a team to manage a collection of Company data models.      Develop integrations, modify existing pipelines, and facilitate the creation of new data sets.      Participate in analysis and engineering projects including data mining, machine learning (ML) modeling, cluster analysis, associative analysis, forecasting and classification.      Build and maintain large scale distributed computing and data architectures.      Fulfill mission statement by performing job duties with a high level of customer service while contributing to a positive team spirit.      Special projects and other duties as assigned.        Supervisory Responsibilities      This job has no supervisory responsibilities.     Education and/or Experience     Bachelor's degree from four-year college or university in computer science, information systems, operations research, mathematics, statistics, or a related field and three to five years of related experience; or equivalent combination of education and experience. Experience working with T-SQL, MySQL, SparkSQL or other query language required. Experience with the following is desired: SQL Integration Services, Azure Data Factory, MSSQL Databases, Databricks, Python, C#, PowerBI.     Physical Demands     The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by a Teammate to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.     While performing the duties of this Job, the Teammate is regularly required to sit; use hands to finger, handle, or feel and talk or hear. The Teammate is occasionally required to stand; walk; reach with hands and arms and stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The Teammate must frequently lift and/or move up to 25 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception and ability to adjust focus.     Work Environment     While performing the duties of this job, the Teammate regularly works in an office setting. The noise level in the work environment is usually moderate. Christensen Farms is one of the largest, family-owned pork producers in the United States, marketing approximately 3 million hogs per year. Headquartered in Sleepy Eye, Minnesota, the company operates throughout the Midwest with facilities in Minnesota, Iowa, Nebraska, Illinois, and South Dakota. Christensen Farms owns four feed mills, manages 145,000 sows on 44 farms, and oversees more than 350 nurseries and grow-finish sites. The company employees nearly 1,000 people and maintains 1,500 contract partnerships.          The company is vertically integrated with a strong presence across the pork value chain - from farm to fork. Christensen Farms is the largest shareholder of Triumph Foods LLC, a producer-owned primary pork processing plant in St. Joseph, Missouri. In turn, Triumph Food members own 50 percent of Daily's Premium Meats, a specialty pork processor bacon and other premium pork products. Triumph Foods also holds a 50 percent partnership in Seaboard Triumph Foods, LLC of Sioux City, Iowa, a primary pork processing plant.          Position Overview & Responsibilities     The Data Architect is responsible for visualizing and designing the organizations enterprise data management framework. This individual will work closely with cross functional teams to continuously optimize timelines, processes, and system automation in supporting management reporting and analytical processes. You will be an advocate for the effective use of data and lead a culture of data-informed decision making. Additionally, this position serves as level 3 employee support for decision science services across the organization.          Major Areas of Accountability         Defining the data architecture framework, standards, and principles, including modeling, metadata, security, reference data, and master data.      Develop business relationships. Understand business problems and work with the team to solve them through data and analytics. Collaborate and build relationships across all levels of the organization.      Translating business requirements into technical specifications, including data streams, integrations, transformations, databases, and data lakes.      Defining reference architecture, which is a pattern others can follow to create and improve data systems.      Defining data flows including which parts of the organization generate data, which require data to function, how data flows are managed, and how data changes in transition.      Provides 3rd level employee support for decision science services.      Works closely with application and technical teams to ensure that current and future services meet data architecture requirements.      Research tools, disciplines and industry trends and recommend improvements for team or company consideration.      Advocate, proliferate, and educate the business on the data assets we have and how to leverage data for decision making.      Other duties assigned within the scope, responsibility, and requirements of the job.        Education, Training and Experience Requirements:         Minimum formal education required: Bachelor's degree in data and analytics or an IT related discipline or 6+ years of equivalent work experience.      2 or more years of experience in a corporate IT Team environment.      Exceptional technical skills required. Cloud based tools (Power BI, Data Factory, Databricks, Snowflake, H20.ai, Excel, database management, etc.). Programming/scripting experience (SQL and HTML) and working knowledge of the software development life cycle.      Clear, concise, and precise written and verbal communication skills to effectively communicate with people of various backgrounds including non-technical audiences.      Strong solution-oriented approach to team problem solving.      Ability to multi-task and to prioritize objectives, anticipate situations and take quick action.      Computer skills required: Working knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite including Visio      Strict adherence to company confidentiality and ethical standards.        Additional Desirable Skills/Qualifications         Certifications in any of the following are a plus: Data Architecture (DASCA, TOGAF, etc.), ITIL.      Artificial intelligence technologies (Machine Learning, Predictive Analytics, etc.).      Enterprise application experience      Cloud technologies (Public, Private, Dedicated, Hybrid).      Experience in Level 2 and/or Level 3 employee support (Freshservice or similar ITSM tool).      Employee computing devices including Windows, Android, and iOS.      Experience working in an agricultural business, particularly the swine industry.

job_title: Sr. Data Analytics Analyst – Fraud Prevention
job_Description: Sr. Data Analytics Analyst – Fraud Prevention  - (062604) At Bank of the West, our people are having a positive impact on the world. We’re investing where we feel we can make the most impact, like advancing diversity and women entrepreneurship programs, financing for more small businesses, and promoting programs for sustainable energy. From our locations across the U.S., Bank of the West is taking action to help protect the planet, improve people’s lives, and strengthen communities. We are part of BNP Paribas, a global leader supporting the UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). Yes, we’re a bank, but as the bank for a changing world, we are continually seeking to improve the ways we help our customers, while contributing to more sustainable and equitable growth.  Job Description Summary  The Sr. Data Analytics Analyst – Fraud Prevention is responsible for sourcing system data from structured and unstructured datasets, anomaly detection, scripting task automation, data extraction design, coding, and data modeling. As a member of Fraud Prevention the Sr. Data Analyst will collaborate across business lines to collect, organize and analyze data from several source systems within the Bank. You will analyze large, complex structured/unstructured data sets in order to extract insights using SAS/ SQL, statistical analysis methods (Decision tools, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting), and/or machine learning techniques with various tools including Open Source methods. This position will focus on design and implementation of fraud prevention analytics and strategies, specifically focused on payment fraud for digital and non-digital channels. You will be responsible for developing sophisticated fraud strategies as it relates to fraud risk exposure. You will proactively identify trends, perform root-cause analyses, draw meaningful conclusions and provide change recommendations to senior management. You will assess strategy change recommendations and evaluate performance post-implementation, revising as needed to support budgeted fraud loss. The team member will collaborate with other Fraud Prevention team members and business product owners on new product initiatives with fraud impacts.  Essential Job Functions  Oversees the business line's data analytics fraud strategy. This may include recommending and developing of related programs for the business line.  Identifies data analytics opportunities through exploratory data analysis (EDA). Designs, and executes scalable, fault tolerant ETL utilizing the department's various computer software packages within established deadlines.  Perform data mining, relating, modeling, profiling, and feature engineering of complex, noisy and large data sources.  Develops data mapping and transformation rules and detailed designs based on system and business requirements. Creates, prepares, and documents detailed specifications of the information systems utilized to extract data.  Analyze the effectiveness of existing fraud models and oversee the design, development, and management of new fraud rules and models.  Analyzes and recommends business, technology, and process improvement opportunities. Utilize automation tools to schedule, execute and monitor.  Maintain the quality control and auditing of source data to ensure the accuracy and quality of data.  Work with cross-functional teams to develop, implement and maintain effective risk management programs to align with the business needs. Identify and quantify levers to help move key metrics. Recommend which product features to build and why. Use experimentation to measure the impact of our initiatives, features, & rules.  Develop automated key performance dashboards.  Work with technical and non-technical stakeholders to enhance analysis with subject matter expertise. Develop visuals and presentations that “tell the story of the data” and conceptualize complex data science techniques in layman’s terms.  Makes recommendations to management for improvements to based-on data trends.   Other Job Duties  Serves as the data analyst lead on strategic fraud prevention projects.  Participate in integration task forces for strategic projects  Understand and applies project management techniques in managing work efforts   Performs other duties as assigned. Qualifications Knowledge of the fraud management life cycle and industry trends.  Experience in developing fraud models from inception to business impact  5-7+ years of directly related experience in statistics, information security, financial services, information technology, or data analytics for bachelors and master’s degree respectively.   Education  Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field (Math, Economics, Statistics, Computer Science, Engineering)*   Skills  Experience cleansing data and developing features, dealing with poorly structured or incomplete data and enhancing data with outside sources  Knowledge of SQL structured query language. Understanding of various statistical techniques and experimentation analysis workflows. Knowledge of programming skills such as Python, R, machine learning techniques and other scripting and statistical tools  Knowledge of Splunk and fraud alerting and case management platforms  Ability to condense information and transform technical data into easily understandable concepts for the business units.  A problem-solving mindset and a willingness to step outside your lane when needed   Demonstrates a strong sense of urgency and is able to work in a fast-paced, ever-changing environment with a strong focus on fraud risk mitigation and customer experience.  Ability to adjust to rapidly changing fraud environment and prioritize deliverables.  Understanding of financial industry, FinTech, risk management, fraud, and/or information security.  A team player attitude with the ability to communicate clearly with both technical and non-technical stakeholders   Equal Employment Opportunity Policy  Bank of the West is an Equal Opportunity employer and proud to provide equal employment opportunity to all job seekers without regard to any status protected by applicable law. Bank of the West is also an Affirmative Action employer -Minority / Female / Disabled / Veteran.  Bank of the West will consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance subject to the requirements of all state and federal laws and regulations. Their engineering, analytic, and operations teams do amazing work to underwrite customers, generate competitive offers, thoroughly and thoughtfully inspect homes, and to support and service their customers in their new homes. Cognitive Neuroscientist (Data Scientist)   About Intheon   We have an exciting opportunity available for the right person to join us at Intheon, a San Diego based startup powering the practical application of neurotechnology in everyday life. We are pioneering a comprehensive platform for neural and biosignal processing and multi-modal analytics. Our platform, products, and automated workflows are used by leading companies and research institutions around the world to accelerate scientific R&D in areas such cognitive state decoding, neural biomarker discovery, exploratory analysis, hypothesis testing, scientific validation, and statistical and machine-learning analyses, real-time cognitive measures, etc. Our real-time data processing and BCI technology stack empowers developers to create transformative brain- and body-aware applications impacting health and wellness, human performance, learning, experiential technology, and more.   To learn more about Intheon’s vision, visit our website at www.intheon.io, as well as these resources :      Spotlight talk at BrainMind Summit @ MIT:     https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ArgM7henCjo      Talk at Transformative Technologies Conference 2020:     https://vimeo.com/480503329   Responsibilities      You will develop processes and pipelines for state-of-the-art brain- and biosignal processing and analysis (EEG, NIRS, ExG, eye tracking and others) for a variety of study and statistical designs, both for post-hoc analysis and real-time uses.    Most of your work will be on workflows used in production by clients, in Intheon’s products (NeuroPype, NeuroScale), and in in-house R&D, and will leverage the Python ecosystem, with occasional limited use of MATLAB or R tools.    Working with an interdisciplinary team, you will continuously expand your skill set and bridge between neuroscience, statistics, signal processing, machine learning and other disciplines, follow current research and findings in the neurosciences, and help distill these findings into a new generation of automated, robust, and large-scale processing suites for brain- and biosignal data.    You will also advise on and contribute to experimental designs for neuroscience research and validation studies (in-house or in collaboration with clients and partners).    You will contribute to the extension of Intheon’s software stack and product platform through the development, implementation, and validation / testing of published and pre-publication methods.     Professional Requirements      Doctorate (Ph.D.) degree or Master’s (M.S.) degree with equivalent years of experience in one of Cognitive Science, Computational Neuroscience, Electrical Engineering / Computer Science, Statistics, Theoretical Physics, or a related field.    Excellent communication skills, ability to self-manage projects, and motivated team player.    A desire to thrive and grow in a fast-paced and challenging high-tech startup environment working on advanced research projects.    Professional conduct respecting HIPAA and other applicable regulations, as well as confidentiality requirements of Intheon’s customers and partners.    Commitment to maintaining an open, welcoming, harassment-free, and equal-opportunity workplace.     Technical Requirements   Required skills:      Demonstrated solid knowledge of neuroscientific principles, conceptual models, and current literature. Track record of peer-reviewed scientific publications.    Familiarity with current-generation neural data analysis techniques, particularly related to electrophysiology (e.g., spectral analysis, source estimation / localization, functional / effective connectivity, multi-subject analysis, artifact removal). Experience with other neural and non-neural modalities is a plus.    Solid programming skills (clean, well-documented and well-tested code).    Prior experience working with Python data science tools (e.g., numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib, jupyter, statsmodels, etc.).    Demonstrated solid understanding of, and prior experience working with, various general-purpose signal processing techniques (e.g., spectral analysis methods, filter designs, linear component analysis methods).    Firm understanding of the inner workings, assumptions, and applicable range of various statistical models, including commonly-used frequentist and Bayesian models, and demonstrated experience applying such models. Comfortable applying statistical validation techniques and criteria.    Solid grounding in common human-subject experiment paradigms and experiment design principles for eliciting neural or behavioral responses.    Excellent problem-solving skills, knack for abstract mathematical thinking (e.g., vector/matrix/tensor data, high-dimensional spaces, probability distributions, etc.).    Excellent English verbal and written communication skills.    High-quality clear writing for contributions to scientific manuscripts, technical reports, technical documentation, and user guides.    Able and willing to fill any knowledge gaps quickly and to learn the necessary theory and tools.     Expertise in one or more of the following areas is a plus:      Applying hierarchical Bayesian models, related estimation/inference techniques (samplers, variational Bayes, etc.) and popular tools (e.g., Stan, PyMC3, etc.).    Adaptive/online statistical signal processing and the underlying principles (e.g., RLS, Kalman filters, etc.).    Sparse signal processing / modeling (e.g., compressive sensing, structured sparsity).    High-performance computing tools and techniques in Python (e.g., jax, cupy, dask). Julia familiarity a plus.    Machine learning and/or deep learning (overfitting, cross-validation, regularization / priors, optimization, etc.).     Job Type: Full-time, can be remote if located in the U.S. or Canada.   Intheon is fully committed to the principle of equal opportunity employment for all. We welcome all applicants, and each applicant is considered for employment without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran, disability status, or any other status protected by applicable laws and regulations.   Note:  Intheon   will not sponsor applicants for work visas (e.g. H-1B) for this position. Research Director  FSR Research Director    Summary:  The Foundation for Sarcoidosis (FSR)  Research Director  will be responsible for leading the execution of FSR’s strategic and operational plans for research development and growth. The Research Director oversees all aspects of FSR’s research department including FSR grant-giving programs, FSR’s patient registry, institution and researcher relations, clinical trial development and recruitment support, and research stakeholder relations with industry, patient-leaders, the NIH, and regulators. The Director is a highly motivated, creative leader dedicated to advancing sarcoidosis research to improve the lives of those living with sarcoidosis.   Reporting Directly to the Chief Strategy Officer, the Research Director is responsible for facilitating, tracking, reporting on, expanding, and optimizing the impact of FSR funding for sarcoidosis research. The   Director will provide strategic input on how to accelerate sarcoidosis research and generate the most significant return on investment for FSR, study sponsors and other funders. The Director will identify, build, and grow FSR’s relations with industry partners, researchers, KOLs, and other entities in a position to advance sarcoidosis research. The Director is responsible for growth, development, and management of FSR’s research team including Research Manager, Research Coordinator, and vendors, consultants and interns.   About the Foundation for Sarcoidosis Research (FSR)    Established in 2000, The Foundation for Sarcoidosis Research (FSR) is the leading international nonprofit organization dedicated to finding a cure for sarcoidosis and improving care for sarcoidosis patients. FSR is based out of Chicago. Since inception, FSR has fostered over $5 million in sarcoidosis-specific research efforts and has worked diligently to provide resources to thousands. For more information and to join our community, visit www.stopsarcoidosis.org.   Remote work is possible.    Job Description:       Advance FSR research program growth, impact, and exposure in collaboration with FSR’s Development and Communications Teams, Chief Executive Office (CEO), and Chief Strategy Officer (CSO).    Manage research agenda and providing strategic input on FSR’s research strategy working closely with FSR’s Scientific Advisory Board (SAB), CEO, CSO, and Governing Board of Directors.    Continuously survey the research landscape to identify new and innovative strategies for accelerating sarcoidosis research.    Manage, increase patient participation, and grow industry and researcher utilization of patients to advance sarcoidosis research.    Manage and grow utilization of FSR’s patient registry.    Build, maintain, and expand relationships with potential funders, clinicians, researchers, industry partners, and other stakeholders key to advancing FSR’s mission.    Manage the FSR research portfolio, budgets, contracting, deliverables tracking, and reporting.    Communicate regularly with clinical investigators, clinical site coordinators, regulatory and safety monitoring staff, laboratory personnel, data coordination center personnel, data analysts, biostatisticians, clinical research coordinators, industry leads and funders, and administrative staff to identify and facilitate progress in sarcoidosis research.    Facilitate and grow FSR Scientific Advisory Board (SAB) and researcher partnerships.    In collaboration CSO, develop RFP/RFQ proposals, fee-for-service proposals, white papers and concept papers.    Serve as FSR representation for research programs to internal and external stakeholders, as needed.    Supervise and mentor research staff to reach ambitious goals.    Other duties as required.     Required Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities :      Masters Degree, MD, or PhD; preferred in biomedical sciences or public health.    Understanding of immunological diseases, rare disease research and epidemiology, and multi- system chronic illness.    3-5 years’ experience in initiating new strategic growth of research portfolio.    3-5 years’ experience working with industry, regulators, and researchers on research advancement.    3-5 years’ experience in the design and implementation of clinical and/or translational research and epidemiologic studies.    Experience with clinical research methods, including studies utilizing randomized controlled trial, cohort, case-control, and case-series designs.    Experience working with federal and local regulations and policies pertinent to research involving human subjects.    Understanding of statistics and experience with statistical analysis, predictive modelling, simulation, and machine learning, health economics, quality, cost, and outcomes measurement, and rare disease epidemiology.    Working knowledge of SQL and/or SAS.    Understanding of database platforms (RedCap, Assessment Center, and ability to query data from various systems).    Strong project management skills    Knowledge of PCs including MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.    Ability to write clearly and concisely.    Prior management experience, preferred.    Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.    Occasional travel, including international, may be required.     Salary will be determined based on experience and knowledge.
